RISK ASSESSMENT

Risk 1: Service Availability
Description: Azure Bastion or VM becomes unavailable
Likelihood: Low (Azure 99.95% SLA)
Impact: Medium (temporary loss of access)
Mitigation:
- Azure provides 99.95% uptime SLA
- Built-in redundancy and failover
- Backup VM can be deployed quickly (2 hours)
- Reports continue running on schedule
Residual Risk: Very Low

Risk 2: Security Breach
Description: Unauthorized access to reporting server
Likelihood: Very Low (no public IP exposure)
Impact: High (data breach, compliance violation)
Mitigation:
- No public IP addresses (90% attack surface reduction)
- Entra ID authentication with MFA
- Network Security Groups restrict access
- Complete audit logging
- Regular security updates
- Azure Security Center monitoring
Residual Risk: Very Low

Risk 3: Data Loss
Description: Reports or data lost due to failure
Likelihood: Low
Impact: Medium (loss of historical data)
Mitigation:
- Azure Backup automated daily
- Geo-redundant storage available
- Version control for scripts (Git)
- 30-day retention policy
- Documented recovery procedures
Residual Risk: Very Low

Risk 4: Compliance Failure
Description: Failure to meet regulatory requirements
Likelihood: Very Low (solution is compliance-ready)
Impact: High (fines, legal issues)
Mitigation:
- Solution designed for compliance (SOC 2, ISO 27001, HIPAA, PCI DSS)
- Complete audit trail
- Encrypted storage and transmission
- Regular compliance reviews
- Easy to generate compliance reports
Residual Risk: Very Low

Risk 5: Cost Overruns
Description: Solution costs more than expected
Likelihood: Low
Impact: Low (costs are predictable)
Mitigation:
- Fixed monthly pricing
- No hidden fees
- Azure Cost Management monitoring
- Alerts for budget thresholds
- Easy to scale down if needed
Residual Risk: Very Low

Risk 6: Performance Issues
Description: Server cannot handle reporting workload
Likelihood: Low (can scale up)
Impact: Medium (slow reports, missed schedules)
Mitigation:
- Start with recommended size (D4s_v3)
